title.34: Adventures on the Planet of the Apes (1975) #4

description.2: Howard sets out to help girlfriend Beverly as she gets into trouble with Turnip-Man. Can Howard and Beverly help this disgruntled, misguided vegetable persona!?
description.7: PANTHER'S RAGE: PART 15: This is it! Black Panther vs. the Klan!
description.11: Daredevil has to prevent a cultish human sacrifice in Central Park!
description.19: Ghost Rider meets a man named Frank Phillips whose hairpin temper is only slightly less terrifying than his vitriolic hate for dolphins!
description.20: The Hulk and the Abomination join forces and take over a Florida space station! 'Nuff said!
description.21: Iron Man finds out that the Red Ghost along with his Super-Apes is too much for one Iron Suit! Plus: The Red Ghost's true goal comes to light! And how will Tony Stark play into it?
description.22: The most chilling, spine-tingling team-up Marvel has ever pulled off! Witness the joining forces of Marvel's horror super stars - MAN-THING! GHOST RIDER! WEREWOLF BY NIGHT! And MORBIUS THE LIVING VAMPIRE!
description.23: Doctor Sun's plans begin to unfold at last! Helpless to stop him, the hunters have no choice but to resurrect the one man that can stand up to Doctor Sun...DRACULA!
description.24: Warlock explores his possible futures with the aid of the Soul Gem. Witness his stunning discoveries!
description.25: Professor X is having nightmares. As visions of inter-galactic war race through his mind, is the Prof merely dreaming...or receiving a psychic S.O.S from an alien race?
description.26: The FF must break up the new friendship between Thing and the Hulk before it's too late! The radiation streaming off the Hulk may be too great for him- how will it affect the Ben Grimm?
description.35: Pete continues to reconcile with MJ after she becomes upset with his recurrent "disappearing act". While interviewing former football star, Dr. Bradley Bolton, Spider-Man becomes involved in a plot of the villain Paine, who has kidnapped Bolton's daughter! What are Paine's demands? And will Spider-Man be able to save both Bolton, and his daughter?
description.36: At the Brand Corporation complex, the five Avengers have broken free. But their movements are being monitored... They're not alone!
description.37: Cataclysmic Kirby action in the mind-bogeling Marvel manner! See Cap and the Falcon battle for their lives against the Trojan Horde!
description.38: The Champions go where no mortals have been before...Olympus, home of the Gods! In a bid to free Hercules, the team must convince Zeus that silver-tongued Pluto is a usurper for the throne. Plus, a stunning battle for the heavens!
description.42: Ex-convict Richard Deacon is transformed into THE FLY by Dr. Stillwell…in a plan conducted by J. Jonah Jameson! What will become of the Daily Bugle’s publisher when his plan backfires?
description.46: Man-Bull loses a crucial trial that will sentence him to years in prison. His lawyer? Matt Murdock.
description.47: Can Captain Marvel withstand the mighty wrath of the Stranger?
description.49: The Avengers must help the Golden Age hero, Whizzer make sense of his disarrayed life. Scarlet Witch has a terrifying encounter with the Living Laser, and her teammates investigate. Plus, Vision gets in trouble with the NYPD!
description.50: War of the Gods! Thor and the mighty Hercules collide to see who is truly more powerful.
description.52: Are you a Jack Kirby fan? This comic (among several others) is definitely the one for you! Written AND drawn by the King, Cap uncovers a UFO holding a beast within...
description.56: Legendary creators Steve Gerber and Frank Bruner present the audacious, quirky, downright filthy Howard the Duck in his own ongoing series! Howard's debut adventure guest stars a plethora of Marvel Heroes- Spider-Man, Conjurer, and many more. Has Howard the Duck quacked up the wrong tree?
description.58: Trapped in a rapidly filling sewer, Spider-Man wishes he had stayed at Ned's engagement party! Peter finds himself in more hot water, when MJ confronts him about his sudden disappearance from the party. Spider-Man tracks the Shocker to the scene of his next crime; New York City's main power plant!
description.59: After busting up a group of train robbers hired by Kang the Conqueror, the three time-traveling Avengers and the heroes of the old west learn how to break into Kang's citadel.
description.60: King Kirby is back to bring you an all new action-packed issue! "Madbomb" can it really destroy the earth? Can Cap and Falc save the world? Read to find out!
description.61: Pluto, King of the Underworld, versus the newly-formed Champions! California's super team must prevent the dual marriage of Venus and Hercules to defend the realm of the Gods. It's no easy task, but with the varied might of this crew, Olympus will tremble!
description.68: PANTHER'S RAGE: PART 14: When T'Challa and Monica Lynne visit her parents in Georgia, the Dragon's Circle and the KKK target the couple!
description.77: The Hulk takes a young orphan to the Wonderland Amusement Park in Florida...where they are met by the Abomination! What will Doc Samson, General Ross, and Clay Quartermain do when two monsters seek revenge?
description.78: What's this? Iron Man rescuing Tony Stark? But Iron Man is Tony Stark. Isn't he? For the shattering answer, you must read!
description.79: Thor's lost in the timestream, having to fight dinosaurs one moment and then soldier from the future the next!
description.80: Dracula is no more...now no one can stop DOCTOR SUN!
description.81: The Fantastic Four are summoned by the government to cure the Hulk once and for all. Can an unlikely string of events surrounding Bruce Banner and the FF produce an unlikely alliance?
description.88: It's a classic case of revenge when Tapping Tommy kidnaps the movie executive that bought out his failing film studio!
description.89: Daredevil takes to space for a battle amongst the stars!  Death-Stalker aims to prove his strength.
description.91: Karen Page becomes Ghost Rider's number one enemy when the Orb seizes control over her body and mind!
description.92: The Hulk meets a young couple, but is soon attacked by the bride's father- The Locust! At the Hulkbuster base, Doc Samson and General Ross put their plans for the Hulk in motion.
description.93: Shell Head versus Firebrand for the life of the world! And it's winner-take- all!
description.94: Half-demon Satana versus full demon Dansker! How will Satana fare against this latest abomination?
description.95: THE FINAL FATE OF DRACULA REVEALED!
description.96: Warlock, Pip, and Gamora face an onslaught of 25,000 Black Knights! Can the cosmic comrades combat these catastrophic odds?
description.97: Introducing the X-Men's new housekeeper, Moira MacTaggart! But is this mysterious woman as domestic as she seems? And what ties does she have to Professor X's past? Meanwhile, Cyclops accidentally releases two demons with his optic blasts.
description.98: The Crusader reveals his true identity and intentions! Can the FF outsmart this foe in order to save New York City's banks?
description.99: The origin of Ulysses Bloodstone, immortal monster hunter, continues! Bloodstone takes down the enchanted Possessor.

1.text: A new foe, the Dark Rider, plans to steal Doctor Doom’s magical energies. Scarlet Witch must team up with Doom to defeat the nefarious Dark Rider.

4.text: Killraven and company deal with the ethicality of protecting a lifeform threatened with extinction.

5.text: Who is Jack of Hearts? Learn his incredible history here! Is White Tiger truly the killer Jack has made him out to be?

6.text: Martial arts madness featuring the first appearance of THE CAT!

7.text: Members of the KKK capture Black Panther, tying him to a burning cross!

8.text: The occultist master Belaric Marcosa summons more demonic nightmares against Werewolf -- some involving Topaz and Lissa!

10.text: Iron Fist and Misty Knight touch down in London…and are immediately attacked by the Ravager! Misty takes some serious blows, motivating Iron Fist to take action. But with the Ravager long gone, will Iron Fist’s man-hunt prove fruitless?

11.text: Daredevil has to prevent a cultish human sacrifice in Central Park!

12.text: The menace of the terrifying Time Twisters reaches its zenith! As Thor and his faithful followers face the fury of their fearsome foes - including a random range of warriors plucked from myriad points in time - the best efforts of the Thunder God and his Asgardian allies appear in vain. Meanwhile, in Asgard, all may not be as it seems as Odin makes an uncharacteristic request.

The menace of the terrifying Time Twisters reaches its zenith! As Thor and his faithful followers face the fury of their fearsome foes - including a random range of warriors plucked from myriad points in time - the best efforts of the Thunder God and his Asgardian allies appear in vain. Meanwhile, in Asgard, all may not be as it seems as Odin makes an uncharacteristic request.

14.text: The tempestuous relationship between Doom and Namor is tested, when the two come to blows over the treatment of Attuma’s men. Little do the villains know that their spat has attracted the attention of one Simon Ryker, a naval man fascinated with cybernetics. Could this mark a new beginning for Doom?

15.text: Doc Strange must face off against his former mentor!

16.text: Introducing Ruby Thursday! Marvel’s strangest villainess makes her enigmatic debut as a headwoman of the Headmen. Doctor Strange suspects Nighthawk’s possessed. And he’s not wrong- Chondu the Mystic has claimed Nighthawk’s body as his own!

17.text: Scarlet Witch has been put on trial during the 1692 Salem Witch Trials! Spider-Man and the Vision face off against Cotton Mather to set her free.

18.text: Enter the Scarecrow! Equal parts demon and man, this new foe will be sure to terrify you.

21.text: Iron Man faces off against one of his most lethal enemies, the armored evil-doer known as The Titanium Man!

27.text: Loose ends from Iron Fist’s past leads to a death battle in his present!

28.text: Introducing Shatterstar! You've never seen anyone like him!

29.text: Mr. Fish may look like a joke, but Power Man comes to learn that his fin-faced villain is no laughing matter!

30.text: Bill Foster is back in action as GOLIATH! But even as he fights crime and makes the news, will his ultimate enemy end up being himself?

31.text: Can Shang-Chi fight his way out of the grip of Darkstrider and his Warlords of the Web?

34.text: Goerge Taylor has been beaten, caged and now he must face the justice of Ape City! Taylor's day in court may turn out to be his last day alive unless he can defend himself against Doctor Zaius!

39.text: On the hunt to track down the Possessor, Daimon Hellstrom learns of the villain's past and origins.

40.text: The adventures of the 31st century's mightiest heroes -- the Guardians of the Galaxy -- continues!

41.text: Night of the She-Cat! Tigra claws her way into her own spine-chilling series in this sensational debut!

42.text: Ex-convict Richard Deacon is transformed into THE FLY by Dr. Stillwell…in a plan conducted by J. Jonah Jameson! What will become of the Daily Bugle’s publisher when his plan backfires?

43.text: This is where it all begins! Get ready for the cosmic origin of Star-Lord! (note: this contains the Star-Lord story only)

44.text: It's Sub-Mariner against U-Man, while the rest of the Invaders fight on another front.  Can Sub-Mariner turn the tides of the war?

45.text: Nighthawk finds himself trapped in the past despite trouble in the present. What disastrous relationship is haunting Kyle Richmond? Doctor Strange and "Nighthawk" do battle on the astral plane. Hulk finds a friend in a baby deer.

46.text: Man-Bull loses a crucial trial that will sentence him to years in prison. His lawyer? Matt Murdock.

47.text: Can Captain Marvel withstand the mighty wrath of the Stranger?

50.text: War of the Gods! Thor and the mighty Hercules collide to see who is truly more powerful.

53.text: Luke Cage and the Thing take on a mighty, towering monster!

54.text: When Cotton Mather summons the Scarlet Witch to Doctor Doom’s castle, she sends out for help, and Spider-Man receives the call.

55.text: Molecule Man's wand doesn't work…or does it? Join Iron Girl and Boyd to find out the TRUE personality-altering power of the Thing's wand!

66.text: Iron Fist takes on the literal Lord of Hell in this jam-packed Kung Fu tale!

67.text: The Master of Kung Fu returns to Manhattan for the first appearance of the MOON SUN'S CIRCUS!

68.text: When T’Challa and Monica Lynne visit her parents in Georgia, the Dragon’s Circle and the KKK attack the couple!

69.text: The Werewolf by Night fights Belaric Marcosa -- but how do you kill someone who's already dead?

71.text: Luke Cage goes to the Land of the Rising Sun! Weapons manufacturer Moses Magnum has kidnapped both Power Man and Samantha Sheridan, an earth scientist. On the Japanese island of Katsyu Shima, Cage has a drag-out, knockdown battle against Magnum for the salvation of the Pacific seaboard!

72.text: The Punisher Becomes a One-Man Invasion!

73.text: Scully and the scientists uncover more time rifts in their prehistoric landscape, yielding confusion and fear. Dr. Raymond Corey grows wary of Scully’s brusque nature. When this ragtag crew discovers a tower of alien origin, what secrets will they unlock? Skull the Slayer versus robot dinosaurs!

74.text: Howard the Duck, President of the United States? A dream for Howard may become reality…unless he’s the victim of a political assassination! Dr. Strange guest-stars in one of the oddest comics around!

75.text: Spider-Man and the X-Men team up in "The Lords of Light and Darkness!"

76.text: The Return of Skar! The Martian warrior is back and badder than ever, this time picking off the Freemen one by one!

79.text:
After learning of the danger posed by the Time Twisters, a trio of
destructive beings from the far-flung future, Thor and his companions agree
to accompany Zarrko the Tomorrow Man on his quest to end their threat before
his world is destroyed. But can a villain from the Thunder God's past be
trusted, especially with the stakes so high? Accompany Thor, the Warriors
Three and the ever-lovely Jane Foster on this time-twisted tale of a
tomorrow that may never come!

83.text: The hunt for Ryker ends here! See Deathlok’s rampage of revenge in “Reflections in a Crimson Eye!”

84.text: Iron Fist and Misty Knight touch down in London…and are immediately attacked by the Ravager! Misty takes some serious blows, motivating Iron Fist to take action. But with the Ravager long gone, will Iron Fist’s man-hunt prove fruitless?

86.text: After the death of Betty Dean, Namor flies off the handle as only his hot temper will allow! Woe be to Dr. Dorcas, Tiger Shark, and Attuma, as the King of Atlantis join’s Doctor Doom in their imminent defeat!

87.text: Eternity plays a cruel cosmic joke on Doctor Strange.

88.text: It's a classic case of revenge when Tapping Tommy kidnaps the movie executive that bought out his failing film studio!

89.text: Daredevil takes to space for a battle amongst the stars!  Death-Stalker aims to prove his strength.

90.text: Upon returning to Earth after taking on the legions of Seth, the Egyptian God of Death, all Thor wants to do is unwind with his friends and best gal pal. However, things don't go as planned when the super-sized Servitor comes literally crashing onto the scene. Featuring Jane Foster, the Warriors Three and Zarrko the Tomorrow Man!
